  "local_port": 56876,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best romantic comedy movies?",
  "response": "Sure! Romantic comedies, often affectionately called \"rom-coms,\" blend love stories with humor to create heartwarming and entertaining films. Here's a list of some of the best romantic comedy movies, spanning classics to more recent releases:\n\n### **Classic Rom-Coms**\n\n1. **When Harry Met Sally...** (1989)\n   - *Starring:* Billy Crystal, Meg Ryan\n   - *Synopsis:* Explores whether men and women can truly be friends without romance getting in the way.\n\n2. **Pretty Woman** (1990)\n   - *Starring:* Richard Gere, Julia Roberts\n   - *Synopsis:* A wealthy businessman hires a spirited escort, leading to an unexpected romance.\n\n3. **Notting Hill** (1999)\n   - *Starring:* Hugh Grant, Julia Roberts\n   - *Synopsis:* A British bookseller's life changes when he falls in love with a famous American actress.\n\n4. **10 Things I Hate About You** (1999)\n   - *Starring:* Heath Ledger, Julia Stiles\n   - *Synopsis:* A modern take on Shakespeare's \"The Taming of the Shrew,\" set in a high school.\n\n### **Modern Favorites**\n\n5. **Crazy, Stupid, Love.** (2011)\n   - *Starring:* Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, Emma Stone, Julianne Moore\n   - *Synopsis:* A middle-aged husband's life changes dramatically when his wife asks for a divorce, leading him to rediscover his manhood with the help of a newfound friend.\n\n6. **The Big Sick** (2017)\n   - *Starring:* Kumail Nanjiani, Zoe Kazan\n   - *Synopsis:* Based on a true story, it follows a couple dealing with cultural differences and a mysterious illness.\n\n7. **To All the Boys I\u2019ve Loved Before** (2018)\n   - *Starring:* Lana Condor, Noah Centineo\n   - *Synopsis:* A high school girl's secret love letters are exposed, turning her quiet life into chaos.\n\n8. **Always Be My Maybe** (2019)\n   - *Starring:* Ali Wong, Randall Park\n   - *Synopsis:* Childhood friends reconnect after 15 years apart, navigating their personal and professional lives.\n\n### **Recent Releases**\n\n9. **Love, Simon** (2018)\n   - *Starring:* Nick Robinson, Jennifer Garner\n   - *Synopsis:* A coming-of-age story about a high school boy navigating life and love while coming out as gay.\n\n10. **Palm Springs** (2020)\n    - *Starring:* Andy Samberg, Cristin Milioti\n    - *Synopsis:* Two wedding guests find themselves trapped in a time loop, leading to unexpected romance and self-discovery.\n\n11. **Ticket to Paradise** (2022)\n    - *Starring:* George Clooney, Julia Roberts\n    - *Synopsis:* A divorced couple teams up to stop their daughter from making the same mistake they think they made 25 years ago.\n\n12. **Marry Me** (2022)\n    - *Starring:* Jennifer Lopez, Owen Wilson\n    - *Synopsis:* A pop star marries a stranger holding a \"Marry Me\" sign at her concert after learning her intended fianc\u00e9 has been unfaithful.\n\n### **Hidden Gems**\n\n13. **About Time** (2013)\n    - *Starring:* Domhnall Gleeson, Rachel McAdams\n    - *Synopsis:* A man discovers he can time travel and uses his ability to improve his love life and relationships.\n\n14. **The Princess Bride** (1987)\n    - *Starring:* Cary Elwes, Robin Wright\n    - *Synopsis:* A fairy tale adventure about true love and overcoming obstacles.\n\n15. **Silver Linings Playbook** (2012)\n    - *Starring:* Bradley Cooper, Jennifer Lawrence\n    - *Synopsis:* Two individuals dealing with personal struggles form an unexpected bond that helps them heal.\n\n### **Animated Rom-Coms**\n\n16. **Shrek** (2001)\n    - *Voiced by:* Mike Myers, Eddie Murphy, Cameron Diaz\n    - *Synopsis:* An ogre embarks on a quest to rescue a princess, discovering love and friendship along the way.\n\n17. **Wall-E** (2008)\n    - *Voiced by:* Ben Burtt, Elissa Knight\n    - *Synopsis:* A lonely robot finds love and embarks on a space journey that decides the fate of mankind.\n\n### **Tips for Enjoying Rom-Coms**\n\n- **Mix It Up:** Explore different eras and styles to find what resonates with you.\n- **Revisit Favorites:** Classic rom-coms often have timeless themes and humor.\n- **Watch with Friends or Loved Ones:** Sharing laughs and heartfelt moments can enhance the experience.\n\nWhether you're in the mood for timeless classics, modern love stories, or something in between, there's a romantic comedy out there for every taste. Enjoy your movie nights!",
